This is my opinion on all 5 chapters.  Psychologically the game was an unpleasant surprise, a few parts really disturbed me (the hospital guard was the worst), I was completely stumped a few times and the gore was over the top.  Overall, I LOVE IT! The artwork is cute & frightening, the story was believable and crazy. I really wish there had been a hundred chapters. The only downside for me was the price, for about $10 dollars, the game should have been a bit longer. I understand the work involved in doing hand drawn graphics and the time to create the story and puzzles, but the price almost kept me from playing the game to begin with. I would have felt better paying $7 for all chapters in one game, but it is what it is. I made the decision to purchase it and I'm satisfied.
